{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1778377987263,"sessionID":"ses_1f06982f9ffe6aylIGUSR0oXsG","part":{"id":"prt_e0f9694be001Lmsjt39ox1j4as","messageID":"msg_e0f96924f001dPo6rC2e6s2v2O","sessionID":"ses_1f06982f9ffe6aylIGUSR0oXsG","snapshot":"1688b33f72daa2ee3edcb26edb1a45f09e7c927d","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778377988651,"sessionID":"ses_1f06982f9ffe6aylIGUSR0oXsG","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_hPxNMQxtoNfSXwmuKbuN7KWy","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/__issue_context__.json","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/__issue_context__.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"body\": \"A few of the root unsatisfiable classes found in the merge product of Uberon and ZFA are caused by what I believe are simple errors that are entirely internal to Uberon (and that are merely revealed by the merge with ZFA).\\r\\n\\r\\n# uvea\\r\\n\\r\\n[uvea](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001768) is said to be [part_of](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050) the '[anterior segment of eyeball](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001801)', which is defined as “any of the parts of the eye that lie in front of, or ventral to, the lens (inclusive)”.\\r\\n\\r\\nThat doesn’t sound correct as, from what I can see, the uvea clearly appears to extend dorsally relative to the lens (if only by its '[optic choroid](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001776)' part, which is incidentally said to [overlap](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002131) the '[posterior segment of eyeball](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001802).\\r\\n\\r\\nThe [uvea](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001768) [part_of](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050) some '[anterior segment of eyeball](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001801)' axiom should be removed – possibly replaced by a relationship to a larger structure, though this may not be needed since there is already axiom stating that [uvea](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001768) '[contributes to the morphology of](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002433)' some '[camera-type eye](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0000019)', which should be enough.\\r\\n\\r\\n# 'future brain vesicle'\\r\\n\\r\\n'[future brain vesicle](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0013150)' (no text definition) is classified as an '[open anatomical space](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0010064)', ultimately an immaterial anatomical entity.\\r\\n\\r\\nThat does not seem consistent with Uberon’s “habits” of representing most anatomical cavities or spaces with terms representing the (material) structures that make them (plus optionall... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n3:   \"comments\": [\n4:     {\n5:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd86gsdQ5\",\n6:       \"author\": {\n7:         \"login\": \"github-actions\"\n8:       },\n9:       \"authorAssociation\": \"CONTRIBUTOR\",\n10:       \"body\": \"This issue has not seen any activity in the past 6 months; it will be closed automatically one year from now if no action is taken.\",\n11:       \"createdAt\": \"2025-03-04T02:18:35Z\",\n12:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n13:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n14:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n15:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n16:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3354#issuecomment-2696008761\",\n17:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n18:     }\n19:   ],\n20:   \"title\": \"ZFA/Uberon issues: simple errors in Uberon\",\n21:   \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3354\"\n22: }\n\n(End of file - total 22 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"body\": \"A few of the root unsatisfiable classes found in the merge product of Uberon and ZFA are caused by what I believe are simple errors that are entirely internal to Uberon (and that are merely revealed by the merge with ZFA).\\r\\n\\r\\n# uvea\\r\\n\\r\\n[uvea](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001768) is said to be [part_of](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050) the '[anterior segment of eyeball](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001801)', which is defined as “any of the parts of the eye that lie in front of, or ventral to, the lens (inclusive)”.\\r\\n\\r\\nThat doesn’t sound correct as, from what I can see, the uvea clearly appears to extend dorsally relative to the lens (if only by its '[optic choroid](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001776)' part, which is incidentally said to [overlap](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002131) the '[posterior segment of eyeball](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001802).\\r\\n\\r\\nThe [uvea](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001768) [part_of](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050) some '[anterior segment of eyeball](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001801)' axiom should be removed – possibly replaced by a relationship to a larger structure, though this may not be needed since there is already axiom stating that [uvea](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001768) '[contributes to the morphology of](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002433)' some '[camera-type eye](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0000019)', which should be enough.\\r\\n\\r\\n# 'future brain vesicle'\\r\\n\\r\\n'[future brain vesicle](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0013150)' (no text definition) is classified as an '[open anatomical space](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0010064)', ultimately an immaterial anatomical entity.\\r\\n\\r\\nThat does not seem consistent with Uberon’s “habits” of representing most anatomical cavities or spaces with terms representing the (material) structures that make them (plus optionall... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n  \"comments\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd86gsdQ5\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"github-actions\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"CONTRIBUTOR\",\n      \"body\": \"This issue has not seen any activity in the past 6 months; it will be closed automatically one year from now if no action is taken.\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2025-03-04T02:18:35Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3354#issuecomment-2696008761\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    }\n  ],\n  \"title\": \"ZFA/Uberon issues: simple errors in Uberon\",","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"__issue_context__.json","time":{"start":1778377988640,"end":1778377988650}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09d353198056791b0169ffe504042881959bc501efc9f65fe3"}},"id":"prt_e0f969802001gRDJMZuK1nYlJ3","sessionID":"ses_1f06982f9ffe6aylIGUSR0oXsG","messageID":"msg_e0f96924f001dPo6rC2e6s2v2O"}}
